      "content": "wait, so you're saying the \"intent is inherently good\" but then you say \"the current overreach is a clear example\" of bad outcomes. that sounds like you've already decided one side is right and the other is just messing up the process. \n\nif the movement is actually causing more harm through censorship and dogmatism, shouldn't we stop calling its intent \"inherently good\" and just call it what it is? it feels like you're defending the ideology while just criticizing the method.",
